1
00:00:01,708 --> 00:00:08,041
After they took me out of solitary
confinement, they took me to another prison

2
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:12,583
They blindfolded me and took me to another
prison, then we walked, and I stayed there

3
00:00:13,458 --> 00:00:16,541
I don’t know exactly where that prison was
because they drove me around for about two hours

4
00:00:17,708 --> 00:00:22,041
They took me to the prison, and after I got out, they drove me home

5
00:00:22,958 --> 00:00:26,958
They said, this is enough, you’ll go home, but
don’t cause any trouble, and things like that

6
00:00:27,291 --> 00:00:35,208
I left, but after some time I couldn’t
stay here, I couldn’t live among them

7
00:00:36,916 --> 00:00:41,208
I left for Turkey, and from there went to Germany

8
00:00:43,541 --> 00:00:48,583
I stayed in Germany for four years,
and after the liberation, I came back here

9
00:00:50,083 --> 00:00:52,833
Interviewer: Tell us what happened to you in Germany?

10
00:00:53,041 --> 00:00:56,875
In Germany, about six months after I arrived there

11
00:00:57,500 --> 00:01:02,375
They filed a lawsuit against me on charges
of possessing a weapon and terrorism

12
00:01:04,458 --> 00:01:08,500
Because I had been here and had fought for the Free Syrian Army

13
00:01:09,708 --> 00:01:16,458
They considered that fighting against the regime was
with Jabhat al-Nusra, not with the Free Syrian Army

14
00:01:18,291 --> 00:01:23,000
I was imprisoned for one and a half
years in Germany, in the city of Dortmund

15
00:01:25,833 --> 00:01:33,666
I was released after being sentenced to three years with
suspension, except for the days I had already spent in prison

16
00:01:35,125 --> 00:01:41,958
I left Germany and returned to Turkey, and stayed there

17
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,875
For about nine months, then I returned to Syria

18
00:01:43,958 --> 00:01:47,000
Interviewer: How do you feel standing
now in the place where you were imprisoned?

19
00:01:48,458 --> 00:01:54,666
My feeling at this moment, in this place
where I was imprisoned, is indescribable

20
00:01:55,625 --> 00:02:03,291
I still feel the awe of this place—I’m still afraid of it to this day
